<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Congeal" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Congeal,</orth> 1) trans. to coagulate, to make to freeze: <cit><quote>sadness hath --ed your blood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.2.134" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 134.</bibl></cit> -- 2) intr. to coagulate, to freeze: <cit><quote>lest zeal, now melted . . ., cool and c. again,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.479" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 479</bibl></cit>. -- Partic. <cit><quote>--ed: blood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1122" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1122</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. luc 1744" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1744</bibl>. <cit><quote>ice,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.2.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 2, 118</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ed white, high Taurus' snow,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 141</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>flaws,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.4.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 4, 35</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>blood,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.3.52" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 3, 52</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.2.37" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 2, 56</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>